<br>
<br>
<br>
       Well, as the subject states, I'd like to introduce myself to you. My name is Tricia, and I am currently a 16th lvl Necromancer of the Tier'Dal, in eternal service to the Father, Innoruuk. Having heard tales of a group not afraid to flaunt their obvious dark superiority in the faces of the lesser races, I was intrigued. So, after a period of covert information gathering, I decided to make this attempt to join your fellowship. My goals are simple: The complete and utter subversion of the Halfling race. Ugh! Little furry mongrels. I place them in the same category as gnolls and goblins and orcs. My power lies in hate. Therefore, the more that hate me, the more power I amass. Druids, Rangers and their pets, the treants; they will know hate when in my presence. Even the Paladins of the Queen of Love, Erollisi Marr, will lose sight of their religious belief and burn with the hatred that can only serve to glorify the Father. Day by day, with every sacrifice I offer to our Lord, my power grows in direct proportion to the hate that burns ever hotter in my breast. Members of the Council, consider my application. Let us join forces and combine our resources to bring <b><i>ALL</b></i> the lesser races beneath our collective heel, where they belong! <br>
<br>
<br>
(ooc)<br>
I am very interested in joining Midnight Council. I am currently a member of Wardens of Norrath, having followed my RL sisters to join. It's not me, to be quite honest. I am a roleplayer, though perhaps a bit more experienced than most expect RPers to be. I am a refugee from Tunare server, having played a Druid to 37, Rogue to 29, and ironically enough, a Paladin and Cleric to 15 and 12, respectively. I came to Torv at the behest of several RL friends (powergamers; you know the "I wanna the the first lvl 50 on the new server" type), who have since moved on (to Tholuxe Paells) which is where I got my equipment. Basically, I saw it as a way to avoid having to camp (my biggest peeve about EQ) so I can just do what I find most fun: RPing my character to the best of my ability. But with the seeming lack of RPers in EQ, a guild that does really appeals to me. After lurking for a few weeks (my sister Taralis is a frequent poster), when I saw Obeah's message on the Torv server board I figured I'd give it a shot. This is my primary character, though I share an account with 3 of my sisters (only 2 of which play actively). Fortunately, our schedules are such that we almost never conflict when it comes to online time. Any questions you might have for me will be readily answered. Until then, I await your decision.....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
